["name" =>"XMind", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"An open source mind mapping tool.", "description"=>"A more elegant way to gather, analyze and utilize knowledge, information and ideas.", "content"=>"XMind is an award-winning (open source) tool you can us to jot down your ideas and brainstorm about their possibilities in a real easy way, creating great looking mind maps. One of the coolest features is the “Idea Factory”, which you can use to collect inspirations when they come to mind. <br />You can easily export your mind maps to Evernote and integrate them in any note or document. XMind also supports exporting to common used file formats like Microsoft Word, PowerPoint, Excel, PDF, RTF, Plain Text, HTML, PNG, JPEG, and more. Best thing to being open source is that XMind is free to download and free to use forever.<br />XMIND.NET", "url"=>"xmind.net", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/xmind.net", "twitter"=>"https://twitter.com/xmind", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.9.1xmind-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"MindMeister", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"The best online mind mapping app currently on the market.", "description"=>"Because of its sleek design and simple interface, MindMeister has been positioned as the number one mind mapping tool available today.", "content"=>"MindMeister is built to facilitate collaboration. MindMeister has been called the number one mind mapping tool available today, mostly because of its sleek design and simple to use interface. MindMeister gives you the ability to quickly develop your own ideas and share your maps to brainstorm and collaborate with others.<br />But MindMap packs many more features: see a full history of changes made overtime, export to various file formats, embed maps on your website and import files and documents you want to use in your brainstorming process from services like Dropbox, Google Drive and Evernote.<br />When you’re finished brainstorming you can use the iPhone and iPad apps to present your ideas right from the app on your AppleTV using AirPlay. You can create up to 3 mind maps with the free MindMeister account, so that should be enough to get you started with your startup idea.<br />MINDMEISTER.COM", "url"=>"mindmeister.com", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/mindmeister", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/mindmeister", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.6.1mindmeister-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Stache", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"A smarter way to bookmark web pages.", "description"=>"Stache makes it quick and easy to collect pages you find useful, interesting or inspiring, in a visual and fully searchable library.", "content"=>"Stache is a great tool to save all web pages that are useful for the development of your startup idea. Use the Stache browser extension to save a web page with just one click, and add them to a fully searchable collection you can check out on your Mac, iPhone or iPad (synced with iCloud).<br />Group and organise bookmarks with folders, collections and tags to index your bookmarks for different subjects. Quickly identify the page you’re looking for using the screenshots of each saved page and search the entire contents of every page to find what you want, when you need it.<br />GETSTACHE.COM", "url"=>"getstache.com", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/getstache", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/getstache", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.5.1stache-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Point", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"Awesome link sharing.", "description"=>"Point is a quick way to share and discuss what you find online.", "content"=>"Point is a simple Chrome plug-in you can use to share links with your teammates. But the great thing about Point is that you can also comment on the content from within the page you are sharing. It works really simple, using the “@” to “point” a page to someone else. When you’ve installed the plugin you create an account and start inviting or adding your teammates.<br />When you’ve found a site you want to share, you simply press Shift+2 and a little pop-up shows up. Here you select who you want to point the url to, hit Enter, and voilá, you just shared it! From here you can talk about the page you shared, select and share pieces of text from within the page and add a tag to the page if you’re collecting stuff within a certain category.<br />Point is only available on Chrome right now, but they are working on multi-browser integration (like Safari) and mobile apps (iOS).<br />GETPOINT.CO", "url"=>"getpoint.co", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/GetPointApp", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/GetPointApp", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.4.1point-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Curator", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"Collect. Organise. Present.", "description"=>"Curator is the No.1 tool for the creative process. From the first fragment of an idea to presentation. Simple, fast, powerful.", "content"=>"Curator is an amazingly simple “modern creativity tool” for your iPhone and iPad. Curator lets you create a visual grid where you can quickly add and reorganise different types of content together, from the very first fragment of an idea all the way through to presentation.<br />Collect and see all of your notes (websites, images or text) in one place and organise all of your content with a simple drag and drop. Use the full screen mode to swipe between notes and even check out all your saved websites with live visual bookmarks. You can also add images from your device or cloud sources like Dropbox and Instagram.<br />CURATOR.CO", "url"=>"curator.co", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/Curatorapp", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/Curator", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.3.1curator-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Experiment Board", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"Test your startup idea without wasting time or money.", "description"=>"Use the lean validation/experiment board to describe, validate and refine your business idea.", "content"=>"The Experiment Board (by Javelin) is tool that was developed based on the learnings from their frst tool, the (Lean) Validation Board, which was used by over 20,000 entrepreneurs around the world. They’ve improved it to get you up and running even faster, teams who use this are ready to run their first Lean Startup experiment within 5 minutes! The Experiment board is free to download (pay with a Tweet) and includes a PDF, a Google Spreadsheet version, and instructions.<br />The PDF document can be printed out as a 60cm x 90cm (2 ft x 3 ft) poster that you can use to put on your (office) wall. If you have a virtual team you can use the included Google Spreadsheet of the Experiment Board to collaborate with your team online.<br />EXPERIMENT BOARD", "url"=>"javelin.com/experiment-board", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/leanstartupmachine", "twitter"=>"http://twitter.com/lean", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.2.1experimentboard-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"germ.io", "categories"=>"Idea Generation", "representation"=>"Get from Idea to Execution.", "description"=>"Too many awesome ideas die in lost notes and cleaned up whiteboards. germ.io lets you capture every eureka moment and helps you execute it.", "content"=>"germ.io is a tool to help you manage your ideas in a better way. Never lose the big picture of your idea, starting from logging the “aha” lightbulb moment that can occur at any time. Validate your ideas and share your vision by showing off the big picture.<br />Evolve your idea by throwing in the next steps and shape up your idea in detail. germ.io gets you on the road to create actionable ideas, helping you define all the how’s, what’s and why’s you need to get going.<br />GERM.IO", "url"=>"germ.io", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/germdotio", "twitter"=>"https://twitter.com/germ_io", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/1.1.1germ-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Dock Name", "categories"=>"Naming", "representation"=>"Go on, ask for a domain", "description"=>"Dock Name is a crowdsourced service that helps startups find a domain name.", "content"=>"Dock Name is a crowdsourced service that helps startups find a domain name, by describing their business/product and get proposals from people that have suitable domains for their needs.<br />The proposals are upvoted by Dock Name’s community, but the final decision is left on the client. The client however is not obligated to buy a domain. Dock Name doesn’t handle the negotiations between the client and the seller, it just connects them.<br />Domain requests can be promoted (bumped to the top) for the duration of one month with a one time payment of $4.99.<br />DOCKNAME.COM", "url"=>"dockname.com", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/dockname", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/dockname", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/2.5.1dockname-150x150.png"],
["name" =>"NameChk", "categories"=>"Naming", "representation"=>"The go to resource for username availability", "description"=>"Check the availability of your username across dozens of the most popular social network websites with NameChk.", "content"=>"Namechk.com was designed to instantly show you if your desired or branded username was available at the majority of the top social networking websites. By typing your username into the “chk” search box, it will query all the social sites listed on the page and display whether the username is taken or available.<br />NameChk enables you to promote your brand consistently by registering a username that is still available on the majority of the most popular sites.<br />NAMECHK.COM", "url"=>"namechk.com", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/namechk", "twitter"=>"https://www.twitter.com/namechk", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/2.3.1namechk.png"],
["name" =>"NameMesh", "categories"=>"Naming", "representation"=>"Name brainstorming simplified", "description"=>"NameMesh helps you in finding a perfect name for your startup or business using an intelligent ranking and classification program.", "content"=>"NameMesh let’s you find a name for your company, app or product with just a simple search. Using ‘Mesh Intelligence’, NameMesh finds name trends and ranks names to get you the most relevant suggestions. Enter the keywords for your startup idea and NameMesh will suggest domain names available with the most common (and new) TLD’s.<br />NameMesh not only shows you basic suggestions, but also short domain names by overlapping the keywords with the tlds, like del.icio.us, foc.us, citi.es etc. Also common alternatives for your domain name are generated, together with domains where other words and popular suffixes like ly, ify are mixed with your entered keywords.<br />NAMEMESH.COM", "url"=>"namemesh.com", "facebook"=>"http://facebook.com/namemesh", "twitter"=>"http://twitter.com/namemesh", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/2.2.1namemesh-150x150.png"],
["name" =>"Naminum", "categories"=>"Naming", "representation"=>"Discover a perfect company name", "description"=>"Naminum is the leading startup, company and website name generator on the web.", "content"=>"Naminum is a company, startup and website name generator designed to make your namestorming sessions smoother. They want to be successful in providing you with THE single name idea that leads you on the right path toward naming your product or company.<br />Enter a word and Naminum uses prefixes, suffixes and replaces letters within your keyword to generate a (huge) list of name suggestions. Didn’t find a satisfactory name? Try with a new word, transform the current one or generate random names for additional inspiration.<br />NAMINUM.COM", "url"=>"naminum.com", "facebook"=>"https://www.facebook.com/usenaminum", "twitter"=>"https://twitter.com/naminum", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/2.1.1naminum-150x150.png"],
["name" =>"Dictionary Domains", "categories"=>"Domain Names", "representation"=>"Legit unregistered domains for your next project", "description"=>"Dictionary Domains offers 14,234 legit, {word}.{tld} domains that you can register and then get back to work on the important stuff.", "content"=>"Dictionary Domains is built and maintained by Justin Thiele. Being a person who loves to make (primarily web) things, he often found himself trying to name products and find domain names. Finding a fitting name is tough, and finding a domain name to match just sucks. Justin is a huge fan of simple {word}.{tld} domains and would happily compromise on the .com extension to get something clean and meaningful.<br />So, that’s the point of Dictionary Domains. To make it ridiculously easy to find simple verb/noun/adjective domains for your next project. Hopefully you find it helpful.<br />DICTIONARYDOMAINS.CO", "url"=>"dictionarydomains.co", "twitter"=>"https://twitter.com/justinthiele", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/3.9.1dictionarydomains-150x150.jpg"],
["name" =>"Lean Domain Search", "categories"=>"Domain Names", "representation"=>"Find a great available domain name for your website in seconds", "description"=>"Lean Domain Search is a domain name generator that helps you find great available domain names for your websites.", "content"=>"Finding an available domain name for your website can be a long frustrating process that makes you want to tear your hair out. Lean Domain Search can help you find a great one in a fraction of the time. One of the most common ways to come up with domain names is to combine two or more words together with one of the words being directly related to the purpose of your website or business. <br />Examples include PasteBin, PlatinumBarbers, Github, BusinessWeek, BackBlaze, VentureBeat, ExtremeTech, SalesForce, SurveyMonkey, and countless others. Lean Domain Search’s domain name generator specializes in coming up with domain names just like these. Just type in a search phrase and the app pairs it with other words to generate a list of possible domain names.<br />LEANDOMAINSEARCH.COM", "url"=>"leandomainsearch.com", "twitter"=>"https://twitter.com/mhmazur", "logo"=>"http://startupstash.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/3.8.1leandomainsearch-150x150.jpg"],
